story.title: Ugly Duckling - Part 2

author.bio: Frank Anthony Polito is an award-winning author and playwright. His published books and plays can be found on Amazon.com. He lives in the Detroit suburb of Pleasant Ridge.

story.storyDescription: Bella would give anything to be pretty. But looks can be deceiving.
story.prePaywallNotification: Bella is now beautiful, but her life is turning ugly. Why? Continue UGLY DUCKLING to find out.

messages.text: When I looked in the mirror this morning‚Ä¶I totally freaked out.
Oh my! It‚Äôs wonderful to see you so happy.
No dear, this is no dream.
I literally had to pinch myself just now.
Don‚Äôt you worry your pretty little head about that.
And now, being beautiful is yours.
But I don‚Äôt understand how this is possible.
All you have to do is believe‚Ä¶
And be willing to pay the price.
My life is going to completely change!
I‚Äôm truly happy for you, dear Bella.
Now go out into the world and be beautiful.
My parents can‚Äôt see me looking like this.
They‚Äôll wonder what happened to their ugly daughter.
Your parents won‚Äôt notice the difference. No one will.
It will be as if you‚Äôve always been beautiful.
I told you not to worry your pretty little head.
Your parents are waiting for you at breakfast.
Bella goes to breakfast and sits down at the table.
Her dad looks up at her with a glowing smile.
Her mom comes over and gives her a kiss.
They don‚Äôt notice anything different about Bella.
But Bella‚Äôs parents seem different to her somehow‚Ä¶
I‚Äôve never seen my parents look at me that way.
Bella starts getting ready for school.
She picks out a dress her mom bought for her last summer, which she never wore.
It‚Äôs a grass green dress with cap-sleeves and lace.
She tries it on and looks in the mirror.
Bella takes a selfie and updates her profile pics.
You‚Äôre the best Fairy Godmother ever.
I never thought I would wear this dress‚Ä¶
But everything looks amazing on me now!
Jake Whitson just added me on FB!
He‚Äôs the captain of the basketball team.
I didn‚Äôt think you knew who I was.
For real? UR the hottest girl in school.
On a Friday night? U wanna hang?
Sure! What do you want to do?
Heard you GET with guys all the time.
Who did you hear that from?
Heard U do it behind the bleachers.
I said I don‚Äôt do THAT.
Hot girls like U R HO‚ÄôS.
Can‚Äôt believe the high school quarterback just friend requested me‚Ä¶
Why wouldn‚Äôt I wanna be friends with the hottest girl in school?
Thought U might wanna hang sometime.
There‚Äôs an exhibit about sound at the art museum.
OK. Maybe we could go to the symphony?
Seriously? U sound like my gramma.
OK. What did you have in mind?
IDK. Thought a hot girl B up 4 some REAL fun.
What do you mean by REAL fun?
What makes you think I hook up?
UR hot. ALL hot girls hook up.
She goes to school, and just as she suspected‚Ä¶
Suddenly, everyone wants to be her friend.
She no longer eats lunch alone.
And she sits with the cool crowd at the football games.
Hey! It‚Äôs Beau Williams. From AP English.
I can‚Äôt think of anyone who deserves it more.
Thanks. I was totally not expecting it.
I don‚Äôt know. I‚Äôm not very popular.
Plus, you‚Äôre a very smart gril.
GIRL. Sorry, can‚Äôt type when I‚Äôm nervous.
I get nervous whenever I text with a pretty gril.
Why do you think you‚Äôre Homecoming Queen?
YOU‚ÄôRE King! Congarts to you, too!
Thanks. Thought for sure Jake or Josh would take it.
No! You deserve it A LOT more than those guys.
Tell me why you think that.
Bella deletes the last part of the text, retypes.
Hey, can I ask you a question?
How come you‚Äôve never talked to me before now?
Doesn‚Äôt make it EZ to talk to pretty GIRLS.
I never know what to say.
So can I ask YOU a question now?
We should go to Homecoming together.
Not cool to leave a dude hanging like this‚Ä¶
My mom just came into my room.
She said we‚Äôre going shopping for my Homecoming dress.
What? You don‚Äôt like to shop?
All pretty girls love to shop.
Ok. I can take a hint.
Wait. I didn‚Äôt answer your question.
If you don‚Äôt wanna go w/ me I‚Äôll just ask someone else.
I‚Äôd love to go to Homecoming with you.
